WEBVTT

02:36.125 --> 02:38.707
Michael, I thought
you were swabbing the deck.

02:38.708 --> 02:40.082
Mum.

02:40.083 --> 02:41.874
When can I do something fun?

02:41.875 --> 02:44.625
Why don't you come up here?
Help me steer.

02:50.375 --> 02:52.582
Try and give it a chance, sweetheart.

02:52.583 --> 02:53.790
When I started sailing,

02:53.791 --> 02:56.499
I had to learn
all the daily chores, too.

02:56.500 --> 02:57.790
But you'll soon
get the hang of it.

02:57.791 --> 02:58.999
And before you know it,

02:59.000 --> 03:01.416
the <i>Peggy Sue</i> will feel
just like home.

03:02.166 --> 03:03.832
Aye aye, Skipper.

03:07.666 --> 03:08.625
Come on, you.

03:10.958 --> 03:13.249
Skipper's hat off.

03:13.250 --> 03:16.707
This is Mum
speaking now, okay?

03:16.708 --> 03:19.582
I know this is a bit of
a re-adjustment, love,

03:19.583 --> 03:21.249
but when your dad and I
lost our jobs,

03:21.250 --> 03:23.082
we wanted to make
the best of things.

03:23.083 --> 03:25.582
- Yeah. That's it, you got it.
-We needed a fresh start.

03:25.583 --> 03:29.500
All of us, together,
exploring the world.

03:30.375 --> 03:31.957
Not quite all of us.

03:31.958 --> 03:33.874
You didn't wanna bring Stella.

03:33.875 --> 03:37.332
Oh, love, we all miss Stella.

03:37.333 --> 03:40.249
But a boat
is no place for a dog.

03:40.250 --> 03:42.665
You know that, sweetheart.

03:42.666 --> 03:45.540
I bet right now she's having
the time of her life

03:45.541 --> 03:47.041
digging up
Uncle Pete's garden.

03:48.375 --> 03:49.915
Michael, look!

03:49.916 --> 03:51.290
Dolphins!

03:58.583 --> 04:01.333
See? It's not
all boring chores.

04:06.000 --> 04:08.499
Hmm. Hi, Dad.

04:08.500 --> 04:10.499
I've got something for you.

04:10.500 --> 04:12.374
Yeah?

04:12.375 --> 04:16.374
It is my privilege
to bestow upon you the honour

04:16.375 --> 04:19.250
of being the keeper of
the log book of the <i>Peggy Sue.</i>

04:25.708 --> 04:26.749
What's a log book?

04:26.750 --> 04:28.290
It's like a diary

04:28.291 --> 04:30.332
of all the fantastic things
we'll see.

04:30.333 --> 04:32.832
And all the exciting places
we'll go.

04:32.833 --> 04:36.957
And here, have a look.
There's a map inside.

04:36.958 --> 04:40.540
You can chart our incredible
journey around the globe.

04:40.541 --> 04:44.665
West Africa, South Africa,
India, Indonesia,

04:44.666 --> 04:46.458
- Australia, Japan...
- Why?

04:47.500 --> 04:48.499
"Why"?

04:48.500 --> 04:49.583
What do you mean, "Why"?

04:53.458 --> 04:55.333
Well, anyway...

04:57.208 --> 04:58.916
It was your mum's idea, okay?

05:15.791 --> 05:16.791
Missed a bit.

05:17.541 --> 05:19.833
Ah!

05:22.541 --> 05:23.874
I'm getting good
at this bit.

05:23.875 --> 05:25.624
Did someone
say "biscuit"?

05:25.625 --> 05:27.500
Okay,
I'll go and get them.

05:36.750 --> 05:38.666
Who took all the biscuits?

05:40.250 --> 05:41.290
Dad, look!

05:41.291 --> 05:43.832
Michael's not fastened.

05:43.833 --> 05:46.124
Oh, Mike. How many times?

05:47.166 --> 05:48.999
You stay clipped all the time.

05:49.000 --> 05:50.332
No exceptions.

05:50.333 --> 05:51.915
Okay?

05:51.916 --> 05:53.375
Aye aye, Skipper.

05:54.666 --> 05:57.999
Becky, I am putting you
on second watch tonight.

05:58.000 --> 06:00.374
I could do a watch, too.

06:00.375 --> 06:02.583
Not just yet, sailor.

06:03.583 --> 06:04.625
Not just yet.

06:26.750 --> 06:28.666
This is amazing.

06:30.541 --> 06:35.124
So many you can barely
make out the constellations.

06:35.125 --> 06:38.457
If you know where to look,
you can use them to steer by.

06:38.458 --> 06:41.582
- Can you?
- Me? (CHUCKLES SOFTLY) Nah...

06:41.583 --> 06:43.832
Your mum's getting
pretty good at it, though.

06:43.833 --> 06:45.165
You can't do it from books.

06:45.166 --> 06:48.332
You see, Becky,
you have to learn by doing it.

06:48.333 --> 06:50.000
Ah, look at that.

06:51.333 --> 06:53.499
Wow.

06:53.500 --> 06:55.832
Now, that is
the magic of the night watch.

06:58.666 --> 07:00.415
Well, I suppose...

07:00.416 --> 07:01.707
Night, Dad.

07:01.708 --> 07:03.040
Are you sure
you're gonna be okay?

07:03.041 --> 07:04.207
Yes, Dad.

07:04.208 --> 07:05.457
All right, all right.

07:05.458 --> 07:07.207
But if you're worried
about anything at all,

07:07.208 --> 07:08.707
you just shout, okay?

07:08.708 --> 07:10.249
- Okay.
- All right.

07:10.250 --> 07:12.125
- Night, sweetheart.
- Night, Dad.

07:34.541 --> 07:37.040
Bloody hell. Don't do that.

07:37.041 --> 07:39.124
You're supposed to be asleep.

07:39.125 --> 07:41.874
If you want,
you could go back to bed.

07:41.875 --> 07:43.457
I'll look after things here.

07:43.458 --> 07:46.457
